176\n337s\n64\u2019s\n51\n20\n169\n33%\n621\n51\n20\n169\n33%\n62%\n18%\n27\n18\n2612\n18%\n26%\nTOBACCO\u2014\nAmer Tobac 140\nReynolds\n137% 138%\n64 64 34\n65\n50,000 SEE PIUS\nGIVE RED HATS\nTO NEW PRINCES\nBy HENRY WOOD\nUnited Press Staff Correspondent\nROME\u2014Amid all the gorge\nous pageantry of Roman Ca\ntholicism, Cardinals Hayes and\nMundelein today received from\nPope Pius XI the red hats that\nsignify their elevation to the\nrank of princes of the church.\n50,000\nFifty thousand persons\nwere\ncrowded into St. Peters, where the\nfinal ceremony, for the first time in\nhistory, was held.\nHundreds of Americans were there\nto see their country-men, who started\nas poor boys on the East Side of\nNew York, receive the highest hon\nors the pontiff can beetow.\nPontiff\nCarried in state on the sedia ges\ntatoria, surrounded by the papal\ncourt,\nHis Holiness entered\nPeters directly from the Vatican.\nSt.\nThere\nawaited him patriarchs,\narchbishops and bishops\nRoman\nprinces, heads of the Jesuits, Bene\ndictines and Franciscans, scores of\nprelates and dignitaries and the en\ntire diplomatic corps.\nHe was assisted to the gorgeous\nred plush and gilded throne facing\nan elaborate enclosure arranged for\nthe sacred college.\nDeans of the college then escorted\nthe new cardinals from the Santa\nPietronila chapel where they had\njust been administered\noaths.\ncardinal\u2019s\nEmbraced\nWhile a choir chanted in the dis\ntance, the American cardinals made\nthree profound reverences.\nEach\nkissed the pontiff\u2019s foot and hand\nand turning, received an embrace\nfrom the cardinals who escorted\nthem.\nThe master of pontifical\ncere\nmonies and the master of the pontifi\ncal wardrobe escorted them to the\nfoot of the throne. There Pope Pius\nbestowed the red hats, first on Mun\ndelein, then on Hayes.\nCHARGE STAMP-STEALING\nHerman C. Davis, 25 years in the\npostal service, was indicted today on\na charge of having stolen a large\nquantity of stamps. Harry G. Trita\npoe was again indicted on a charge\nof false pretenses, alleging that the\ndefendant, posing as a secret service\noperator, gained admission to Wash\nington theaters.\nBOY TO RECOVER\nBernard Garvey, 3, 1\n3516\n1\nllth-st nw, who was knocked i\nunconscious March 3 by an J\nauto near nis home, finally has j\nregained consciousness, it .was t\nsaid today at Emergency hos-\npital. His personal physician,\nDr. Daniel Borden, stated the\nboy probably will recover en-\ntirely. I\nThe duration of Harvey's\nunconsciousness was the long- j\nest known at Emergency, it is\nHis skull was broken in\nsaid.\nsix places.\nSMITHSONIAN MUSEUM\nEXTENDS SCHOLARSHIP\nThe Walter Rathbone Bacon trav\neling scholarship, for study of fauna\nin other countries, has been extended\nto June 1, 1924, the secretary of\nSmithsonian Institution announces.\nThis scholarship makes available\nabout $2400 yearly, which goes to\none individual to pay his expenses\nwhile studying abroad.\nApplicants\nmust detail their plans for the pro\nposed study, the problems involved\nand reasons why it should be under\ntaken. The fund will be awarded for\na term of two years and may be ex\ntended if the incumbent make.- his\ncase strong enough.\nHOUSING SURVEY TOBE\nFINISHED WITHIN WEEK\nA report on the survey of housing\nconditions here, as provided in Sen.\nBall\u2019s\nresolution, which\nwill bear\nlists of every\u2019 vacant apartment room\nand dwelling together with rent\nasked and condition of the property.\nI will be placed in the hands of the\nSenate\nDistrict\nsubcommittee\non\nMarch 31, A. B. Moore, head of the\nspecial investigating committee, -aid\nI today.\nGERMAN ARTIST TELLS\nOF MODERN ART ERA\nArnold\nRonnebeck,\nmodernist\nsculptor of Berlin, last night told\nthe members of the arts committee\nof the Woman's City club \"we are\nnow in the midst of a new era of\nart.\" Theodore Morgan, local artist,\nspoke of the fundamental school and\nasked for the preservation of the\nclassical ideal in art.\nLOCAL CLEARINGS\nClezris today\nWerk azo\nYear azo\n$3.24: 453$ 71\n3 401 1091\n445\n3 0\nNew York Curb\nSTANDARD O\u2014\nAcme Coal.\nAm Haw S S..\nAm I.t Trac.\nBlumenthal Co.\nBridgept Mach.\nBklyn Citv Rwy\nCent C I P.\nColo Power.\n1), I. W Coal.\nDublier Cond..\nGill Safety Raz.\nGlen Alden Coal\nGoodyear Tire..\nHudson Co pfd.\nHudson Manhat\nInercon Rubber.\nMesabi Tron..\nN Y Tel pfd.\nPyrene Mfg..\nRadio.\nRadio pfd.\nReo Motors.\nSouth C Iron.\nStutz Motor\nTob Prod export\nTodd Ship\nUnited Bakers\nUn Shoe Mach.\nWayne Coal\nYet Taxi of N Y\n994\n135\u20194 131\n91\n3\"\n133\n964\n12034 120\u2018s 120's\nn%\nn%\n281\n34\n93\n30\n10 34\nnN\n2814\n34\n927\n273,\n273 14 273\n103\n11%\n28%\n34 i\n927s!\n29\n8644\n10\u2018s\n2112\n12%\n3\u2018\n6;\n853\n10\n2112\n12\u2018s\n314\n6\n273\ni\n863,\n10\n2112'\n12% i\n3\u2018\nI\n1093, 1098 10934\n115\n1134\n11% 1\n4\u2018s 4 4\n4\u2018 4 1-16 4 1-10\n1612\n10\n914\n4 \u20184\n49*\n46\u20191\n35\n52\n307\n16%\n8\n9\n4%\n49%\n46%\n35\n52\n30%\n16%\n10\n9%\n4%\n19%\n46%\n35\n52\n30\u20194\nINDEPENDENT OILS\nArk Nat Gas...\n[Cities Service\ni Mountain Piod\nMutual Oil, vtc.\n0 4\n145\nIS\n113\nSalt Creek Prod 22\u2018\nINDUSTRIALS\u2014\n144\n17%\n11\n22%\n5%\n144\n17%\n11%\n22%\n1\nAnglo Amer Oil\nInter Pet\n16%\n19%\nPrar Oil Gas. 242\nPrar Pipe Line. 10G\nStand Oil of Ind 623\n159\n19\n236\n16%\n19%\n23814\n10412 106\nGO SA\n61%\nStand Oi) of Ky 1091e 109% 10912\nStand Oil of N Y\nVacuum Oil\n43\n643\n4212\n62%\n42\u2019-..\nG4\nMANY AERIALS\nVIOLATE RULES\n1 Most radio aerials strung on house\ntops do not comply with regulations\nadopted by District commissioners\ni last week, fire inspectors and fire\ni men reported to Fire Marshal Sieb.\nOver 600 anteanae were reported\nI\n1 strung lower than seven feet above\nthe roof as prescribed by the regula\n\u2018t... They were ordered removed\nlions.\nio: raised.\nby a fine up to t2i\nLow strung wire;\nViola.\u0964 ms are punishable\non roofs would\nfiremen\nhamper work of firemen and en\ndanger their lives by tripping them\nup and possible sen ling them plung\ning to their deaths from roof tops.\nChief Watson aul\nFiremen will continue their sur\nvey until the entire city ha- been in\nspected.\nNEW VETERANS\u2019 DIVISION\nA new division in the Veterans\u2019\nBureau to handle all matters per\ntaining to guardianship has been\nauthorized.\nIt will function under\nthe control service, headed by Maj.\nDavis G. Arnold, assistant director.\nFLYERS OFF FOR ROME\nLYON\u2014 The\nBritish\nround-the.\nworld fyers took off toward Rome at\n11:05 a. m. today.\n1\nDEATHS\n\nsi.\nFuneral services for A. T. Brooke.\nwho died Tuesday\nat\nGeorge\nWashington university hospital, was\nI held\nthis\nmorning\nat\nGawler\nchapel, and Trinity Episcopal church,\ni Upper Marlboro.\nHe at one time\nheld several office, in Prince Georges\nj county.\nFuneral services for Mrs. Cather\nt\ni ine V. Young, 89, who died Monday,\nwere held\nhome, 2027 Hillyer-pl\nyesterday at her late\nIW.\nBurial\nwas in Oak Hill cemetery.\nFuneral services for Thoma.- Ellis,\nCivil\nwar veteran who died yester\nday at his home, 130 13th-st se, to\nmorrow at 2 p. m.\nHe is a former\ntrea-ury employe and is survived by\nhis\nwidow,\ndaughters.\ntwo\nHe\nsons\nand three\nRock Creek cemetery.\nwill be buried at\nr\u2014\nBRITTEN LOSES VENUS\nRep. Britten, III., has lost\nhis diving Venu.-.\nShe\u2019s nickel-plated.\nSome\nbody last night stole her, at\ntached to the radiator cap of\nhis auto, in front of 1336 New\nHamp-hire-av nw.\nt\n4 INDUSTRIALS\nSET CURB HIGHS\nRy United Financial\nNEW YORK- Four new highs in\nthe industrial section and a general\nforward\nmovement\nin\nthe\nfeatured the curb market today.\noils\nThe\nmarket was buoyant in sections at\ntimes with the turnover heavy. 1\nThe issues to touch new high levels\nwere American Light Traction, up\nto 135F. W. Grand Stores, up\n15* at 4412; Colorado Power, up 1\u20192\nat 34* and Park Tilford Stores,\nup 1% at 304.